Altimo Seeks Independent Management for Turkcell, Milliyet Says

-- B y   B e n   H o l l a n d
-- 
2011-04-09T07:11:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-09/altimo-seeks-independent-management-for-turkcell-milliyet-says.html
Altimo, the Russian phone operator
that’s one of three main shareholders in Turkcell Iletisim
Hizmetleri AS, has no plans to gain control of the Turkish
company and wants it run by independent management, Altimo Chief
Executive Alexey Reznikovich said, according to Milliyet
newspaper.   Altimo wants Turkcell’s minority shareholders to be
represented on the board and sees opposition to the plan from
another shareholder,  Turkey ’s Cukurova Group, and the company’s
Chairman Colin Williams, Reznikovich told reporters in Moscow,
according to Milliyet.  TeliaSonera AB (TLSN) , the biggest shareholder in Turkcell, has
been in a dispute with Cukurova and Alfa over control of the
company for several years.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
